  "text": "For several years, yet another issue of environmental analysis has been gaining more and more importance, namely the influence of a given type of analytical activity on the condition of the environment itself and on the health of employees of analytical laboratories (environmental impact assessment, or EIA). It is connected with attempts being made to introduce commonly known principles of green chemistry and more and more popular principles of green analytical chemistry (GAC) into everyday laboratory practice [CITATION_1] 26] .",
